name: sdc-dot-metadata-ingest
description: Lambda function to capture metadata across the pipeline and ingests into Elasticsearch. This also includes the lambda code for generating the CDO dashboards in Elasticsearch service

name: sdc-dot-batch-creation
description: Lambda function to periodically (based on a cloud watch event rule) create new batch id, push the previous batch id to SQS queue

name: sdc-dot-waze-kinesis-data-persist-to-dynamo
description: Lambda function that is invoked by kinesis stream on a periodic basis to flush out the data records from kinesis stream to Dynamo db table which are later used for manifest generation process

name: sdc-dot-persist-data-to-kinesis
description: Lambda funtion to persist the curated data into Kinesis Data streams

name: sdc-dot-waze-poll-for-batches-to-manifest
description: Lambda function that polls for new batches for which manifest generation process can be generated. Polls the queue and publishes a message to SNS topic.

name: sdc-dot-manifest-generator
description: Consists of source code for creating a manifest file based on the curated dataset records in dynamo db table Consists of source code for creating a manifest file based on the curated dataset records in dynamo db table

name: sdc-dot-waze-close-manifest-pipeline
description: Lambda function to complete the manifest generation state machine. This function deletes the message from the queue after successfully generating manifests for a batch, and publishes the batch id into persistence queue, finally sends manifest generation completed status to SNS topic

name: sdc-dot-waze-poll-for-batches-to-process
description: Lambda function that polls for new batches for data to be persisted into Redshift. Reads the message from queue and sends a notification to SNS topic

name: sdc-dot-waze-get-manifests-for-persistence
description: Lambda function to get the manifest records from dynamo db for a given batch for all traffic types (alerts, jams, irregularities) for which manifest generation process needs to be initiated

name: sdc-dot-waze-data-persistence
description: Lambda function that handles the persistence of waze curated data to redshift. Performs all actions from creating stage tables, persistence to redshift, updating statistics tables for quality checks etc

name: sdc-dot-waze-update-manifest-status
description: Lambda function to update the manifest status, after manifest generation process is completed for tables names alert, jam and jam_point_sequence respectively.

name: sdc-dot-persist-create-cloudwatch-metrics
description: Lambda function to persist pre-persistence and post-persistence metrics to cloudwatch for monitoring and auditing purposes

name: sdc-dot-waze-close-persistence-pipeline
description: Lambda function that is triggered at the end of waze persistence step function workflow. The primary function of this lambda function is to delete the message from queue and publish a notification upon successfully processing each message
